  "expected_convert_fail_note": "Derived from the phase-1 sweep (build/report/m5_sweep.json): each failure's wast2json stderr is recorded in build/report/m5_conversion_report.json. Groups: reference-types/externref syntax (br_table, br_if via typed select, global, imports, linking, ref_*, select, table_*, local_init, local_tee, call_indirect, elem, func, unreached-*, type-equivalence); GC/typed-function-references (call_ref, return_call_ref, br_on_*, type-canon, type-rec, ref_as_non_null); tail-call (return_call, return_call_indirect); multi-memory/memory64-era syntax (memory, table, instance, exports, imports, align 64-bit offset); annotations (annotations, id); bulk-memory/passive segments (data, token); binary-format update beyond pinned WABT (binary, binary-leb128).",
  "judgment_boundaries": {
    "invalid_binary_texts": [
      "constant expression required",
      "start function",
      "type mismatch",
      "unknown function",
      "unknown label",
      "unknown local",
      "unknown table",
      "unknown type"
    ],
    "malformed_binary_texts": [
      "data count and data section have inconsistent lengths",
      "function and code section have inconsistent lengths",
      "length out of bounds",
      "malformed UTF-8 encoding",
      "malformed section id",
      "unexpected end"
    ],
    "trap_texts": [
      "integer divide by zero",
      "integer overflow",
      "invalid conversion to integer",
      "out of bounds memory access",
      "undefined element",
      "unreachable"
    ],
    "exhaustion_texts": [
